The merchant bought himself a jeep and left it near the house. In the evening, a local drunk walks in and sees the 4x4 inscription on the back. Without hesitation, he takes a nail and scratches = 16. In the morning, the evil owner drives the jeep to the service and paints over the scratches. And so it is every day, for a whole week. As a result, the owner of the jeep orders a ready-made inscription 4X4 = 16. Happy goes home and parks the car there near the house.
An alcoholic goes in the evening and sees the inscription 4x4 = 16, takes out a nail and summarizes - CORRECTLY.
